City Court of New York — General Term, November, 1901.

Before Conlan and Hascall, JJ.

Joseph Barondess, Respondent, v. Paul M. Kaminsky et al., Appellants. Appeal from a entered verdict and order denying motion for new trial. William Klingenstein, for appellants; Henry Kuntz, for respondent.

Judgment and order should be affirmed, with costs. No opinion.
